Prophylactic treatment should be attempted for a
minimum of 2–3 months at full dose, before it may
ﬁnally be assessed if it has any effect (unless treatment
is not tolerated due to side effects).
In case of effect, discontinuation should be attempted
every 6–12 months to conﬁrm that the patient still needs
the medication and that the medication remains effective.
Lacking effect from one type of prophylaxis does not
preclude the effect of other types of prophylaxis.
